|19| Brothers, if anyone among you errs from the truth and turns anyone ^with^
him,

# Matthew 18:15
# Dealing With Sin in the Church - "If your brother or sister sins, go and
# point out their fault, just between the two of you. If they listen to you,
# you have won them over.

# James 3:14
# But if you harbor bitter envy and selfish ambition in your hearts, do not
# boast about it or deny the truth.

# Galatians 6:1
# Doing Good to All - Brothers and sisters, if someone is caught in a sin, you
# who live by the Spirit should restore that person gently. But watch
# yourselves, or you also may be tempted.

|20| know that the ^one^ turning a sinner from ^the^ error of his ways will
save ^the^ soul from death and will hide [of ^cover^] a multitude of sins.

# 1 Corinthians 1:21
# For since in the wisdom of God the world through its wisdom did not know him,
